{{Infobox language |name=Latu |states=[[Indonesia]] |region=[[Seram Island]], [[Moluccas]] |ethnicity= |speakers=2,100 |date=1982 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] (MP) |fam3=[[Nuclear Malayo-Polynesian languages|Nuclear MP]] |fam4=[[Central Maluku languages|Central Maluku]] ? |fam5=[[East Central Maluku languages|East Central Maluku]] |fam6=[[Seram languages|Seram]] ? |fam7=[[Nunusaku languages|Nunusaku]] |fam8=[[Piru Bay languages|Piru Bay]] |fam9=East |fam10=Seram Straits |fam11=Uliase (Lease) |fam12=Saparua |iso3=ltu |glotto=latu1237 |glottorefname=Latu }}
'''Latu''' is an [[Austronesian language|Austronesian]] language spoken on [[Seram Island]] in the [[Moluccas]] in eastern [[Indonesia]]. It is linguistically close to [[Saparua language|Saparua]].
