{{au-lang-stub}}

There are dozens of ethnic groups in [[Guizhou]] province of China that are not officially recognized. These ethnic groups and their languages include:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://asiaharvest.org/index.php/people-group-profiles/china/ |title=China |publisher=Asia Harvest |date= |accessdate=2013-07-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130801062653/http://asiaharvest.org/index.php/people-group-profiles/china/ |archivedate=2013-08-01 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gzmw.gov.cn/ShowNews.aspx?NewsID=52|title=贵州省民族事务委员会-贵州省民族识别认定工作|publisher=Gzmw.gov.cn|date=|accessdate=2013-07-19|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120802091338/http://www.gzmw.gov.cn/ShowNews.aspx?NewsID=52|archivedate=2012-08-02|df=}}</ref> *'''[[Caijia language|Caijia]] 蔡家''' *'''Chuanlan 穿兰''': over 300,000 people classified as [[Han Chinese|Han]], in [[Anshun]] Prefecture; many also speak Bouyei and Miao *'''[[Chuanqing]] 穿青''': 500,000–1,000,000 people classified as [[Han Chinese|Han]], mostly in Zhijin and Nayong, but also in Dafang, Shuicheng, Guanling, Qingzhen, Puding, and Liuzhi counties of Guizhou; has some non-Chinese loanwords *'''Limin 里民''': 50,000–100,000 people classified as [[Yi people|Yi]] and sometimes as [[Li people|Li]], in Liuzhi, Guanling, Pu'an, Xingren, Zhenning, and Anlong counties of western Guizhou; most have shifted to Southwestern Mandarin, with few Limin speakers remaining. Also in Qinglong (''Qinglong County Almanac 1993''). Wang (2011) has researched ethnic Limin villages including Fanhua Village 凡化村, Pogong Township 坡贡镇, [[Guanling County]].<ref name="Wang2011">Wang Xianjun [王献军] (2011). [http://wuxizazhi.cnki.net/Search/ZNZX201103011.html 贵州“里民人”探寻.]</ref> *'''Liujia 六甲''': 4,000 (1999) people classified as [[Han Chinese|Han]], in [[Congjiang County]], Guizhou. Hou Jingrong (2009) considers the Liujia language to be a [[Yue Chinese]] dialect.<ref>Hou Jingrong [侯井榕]. 2009. Phonological System and Linguistic Typology of Liujia Chinese Dialect in Sanjiang of Guangxi Autonomous Region [广西三江县六甲话的语言特点]. http://comonca.org.cn/PDF/2009/COMONCA03-010.pdf{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In Guangxi, Liujia is spoken in Sanjiang County (in Guyi 古宜, Zhouping 周坪, and Chengcun 程村) and Rongshui County (in Dalang 大浪 and Danian 大年乡).<ref>{{cite web|author=最近读者 |url=http://chenshihua11.blog.163.com/blog/static/11454460201272083130419/ |title=六甲话简介 - 南岭笛声的日志 - 网易博客 |publisher=Chenshihua11.blog.163.com |date=2012-08-20 |accessdate=2013-07-19}}</ref> *'''[[Longjia people|Longjia]] 龙家''' *'''[[Luren language|Lu]] 卢''': 3,000–6,000 people classified as [[Manchu people|Manchu]], in Dafang, Qianxi (in Fuyuan 附源村 of Jinpo 金坡乡), and Bijie counties, Guizhou; also in Anluo 安洛, [[Jinsha County]];<ref name="Gazetteer">Guizhou Province Gazetteer: Ethnic Gazetteer [贵州省志. 民族志] (2002). Guiyang: Guizhou Ethnic Publishing House [貴州民族出版社].</ref> the Lu now speak Southwestern Mandarin. In [[Qianxi County, Guizhou|Qianxi County]], the ethnic Manchu (pop. 916 as of 1990) are known as Lu'eren 禄额子, Luren 禄人, and Yuanren 原人, and are distributed in Huangni Township 黄泥乡 of Shachang District 沙厂区, as well as Dashui 大水, Gamu 嘎木乡, and Shachang 沙厂镇.<ref>''Qianxi County Almanac'' (1990:157)</ref> Subdivisions include the White Luren 白卢人 and Black Luren 黑卢人.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://222.210.17.136/mzwz/news/21/z_21_46506.html |title=白族家园-讲义寨 |publisher=222.210.17.136 |date=2011-01-28 |accessdate=2013-07-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017095638/http://222.210.17.136/mzwz/news/21/z_21_46506.html |archivedate=2014-10-17 |df= }}</ref> *'''Nanjing people 南京人''': 120,000 people classified as [[Bai people|Bai]], in Bijie, Dafang (in Shagou 沙沟村 and Dongfeng 东丰村<ref>贵州"六山六水"民族调查资料选编. 回族, 白族, 瑤族, 壮族, 畲族, 毛南族, 仫佬族, 满族, 羌族卷 (2008). 贵州民族出版社.</ref>), Liupanshui, Qianxi, Weining, Jinsha, Nayong, Anshun, Qingzhen, and Zhijin counties of western Guizhou; some speak the [[Longjia language]]. Ertang Township 二塘乡, Zhongshan District 钟山区 has a population of 2,262 Nanjingren, with a total of 2,936 in Liupanshui prefecture; historical names include Longjiazi 龙家子/龙架子 and Longgedou 龙格兜.<ref name="Liupanshui">''Liupanshui City Ethnic Gazetteer'' 六盘水市志：民族志 (2003:186-187). {{ISBN|7-221-05533-5}}</ref> Their autonym in Qianxi County is Xienan 写南, and Xiejing 写京 in Dafang County (''Zhenxiong County Almanac'' 1987:447). In [[Xixiu District]], [[Anshun]], the Nanjingren are also called the Yingtian 应天.<ref>''Xixiu District Gazetteer'' 安顺市志：西秀区志 (2007:110)</ref> In Zhenxiong County, Yunnan, their autonyms include Awupu 阿乌浦 and Awudu 阿乌堵 (You 2013:134).<ref name="You2013">You Weiqiong [尤伟琼]. 2013. ''Classifying ethnic groups of Yunnan'' [云南民族识别研究]. Beijing: Ethnic Publishing House [民族出版社].</ref> *'''[[Qixingmin people|Qixingmin]] 七姓民''' *'''Shenzhou 神州''': 4,000 (1999) people classified as [[Han Chinese|Han]], in [[Anshun]] Prefecture; has some non-Chinese loanwords *'''[[Tunbao]] 屯堡''': archaic Chinese dialect spoken in [[Anshun]] Prefecture.<ref>[http://www.zj3mwater.com/YuYanWenXue/2014-01/426987.htm 安顺市天龙镇屯堡方言声韵调系统初探]</ref> Long, et al. (2011)<ref name="Long">Long Yiteng, Wu Weijun, Song Yi, Ming Shengrong [龙异腾, 吴伟军, 宋宜, 明生荣]. 2011. ''A study of the Tunbao dialect of Central Guizhou'' [黔中屯堡方言研究]. Chengdu: Southwest Jiaotong University Press [西南交通大学出版社].</ref> covers the Tunbao dialect of Jiuxi Village, Daxiqiao Township, [[Anshun]] (安顺市大西桥镇九溪村).
{| class="wikitable" |+ Miscellaneous ethnic groups of Guizhou<ref>{{cite web|author=(2010-07-26 12:32:28) |url=http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_5ce6739e0100kqac.html |title=天地革家人之 革家当前的形势、走向定位与工作思路_天地革家人_新浪博客 |publisher=Blog.sina.com.cn |date=2010-07-26 |accessdate=2013-07-19}}</ref> ! Group ! Population ! Official classification ! Distribution |- | Liujia 六甲人 | 152 | Han | Rongjiang County |- | Chenzhou 辰州人 | - | Han | Pingtang County |- | Nanjing 南京人 | 61,171 | Han | Bijie, Anshun, Liupanshui prefectures |- | [[:zh:喇叭苗话|Laba]] 喇叭 | 60,000+ | Miao | Qinglong, Pu'an, Liuzhi, Shuicheng, Pan, Longli counties |- | [[Luobohe Miao|Xijia]] 西家 | 9,000+ | Miao | Kaili, Duyun, Majiang |- | [[Mak language|Mojia]] 莫家 | 17,017 | Buyi | Border region of Dushan and Libo counties |- | [[Qixingmin people|Qixingmin]] 七姓民 | 7,589 | Bai | Shuicheng, Weining, Hezhang counties |- | [[Bunu language|Changpao Yao]] 长袍瑶, Youmairen 油迈人 | 300+ | Yao | Libo, Wangmo counties |- | [[Luren language|Lu]] 卢人 | 7,747 | Manchu | Border region of Qianxi, Jinsha, Dafang counties |- | [[:zh:羿人|Yi]] 羿人 | 1,015 | Gelao | Bijie Prefecture |- | Xialusi 下路司, [[Cao Miao language|Diao]] 刁人 | 984 | Dong | Congjiang County |- | [[Sanqiao language|Sanqiao]] 三撬 | 2,374 | Miao or Dong | Liping County |- | Limin 里民 | 70,000 | Yi | Qinglong, Guanling, Zhenning, Shuicheng counties |- | [[Gelao language|Mulao]] 木佬 | 28,000 | Mulao | Majiang, Duyun, Fuquan, Weng'an counties |- | [[Then language|Yanghuang]] 佯亻黄 | 40,000 | Maonan | Pingtang, Dushan, Huishui, Luodian counties |- | [[Raojia language|Raojia]] 绕家 | 9,000+ | Yao | Majiang, Duyun counties |- | [[Gejia language|Dongjia]] 东家 | 40,000+ | She | Majiang, Kaili, Duyun, Fuquan counties |- | [[Longjia people|Longjia]] 龙家 | 10,000+ | Bai | Bijie, Anshun, Liupanshui prefectures |- | [[Gejia language|Gejia]] 亻革家 | 40,000 | | Huangping, Kaili, Guanling, Shibing counties |- | [[Caijia language|Caijia]] 蔡家 | 20,000 | | Qianxi, Bijie, Nayong, Hezhang, Zhijin, Shuicheng, Liuzhi counties |- | [[Chuanqing]] 穿青 | 600,000+ | Han | Bijie, Anshun, Liupanshui precfectures |}
